## Visualization

With this dataset, I created a VegaLite line plot to show the relationship of the water level in Lake Huron over the years of 1875 to 1972. I also used the built in idyll button function to create two unique buttons. If you click the `Water Level` button, you are able to see the change in water level by color. If you click the `None` button, you can revert back to the original VegaLite plot. I find it interesting how the water level does not have a definite linear trend. I think it would be valuable if there were additional columns on rainfall and heat index in these years to understand how the water level is affected in this way.
 [Color Scheme Source](https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/schemes/)

